  "prompt": "How do I keep Instagram private from Facebook friends and contacts?",
  "response": "Keeping your Instagram private from your Facebook friends and contacts requires a multi-pronged approach, as Instagram and Facebook are heavily interconnected. Here's a breakdown of the steps you can take, along with explanations:\n\n**1. Disconnect Your Accounts:**\n\n*   **From Instagram:**\n    *   Go to your Profile.\n    *   Tap the three horizontal lines (menu icon) in the top right corner.\n    *   Go to \"Settings and privacy\"\n    *   Tap \"Account Centre\" at the very top\n    *   Tap \"Accounts\"\n    *   Remove your Facebook account from the linked accounts.\n\n    *This is a crucial first step.  It stops future automated sharing of activities.*\n\n**2. Change Your Privacy Settings on Instagram:**\n\n*   **Make Your Account Private:**\n    *   Go to your Profile.\n    *   Tap the three horizontal lines (menu icon) in the top right corner.\n    *   Go to \"Settings and privacy\"\n    *   Tap \"Account privacy\"\n    *   Toggle \"Private account\" **ON**.\n\n    *   *This is the most important step! A private account means only people you approve can see your posts, stories, Reels, and your followers/following list.*\n\n*   **Manage Who Can See Your Stories and Reels:**\n    *   Go to your Profile.\n    *   Tap the three horizontal lines (menu icon) in the top right corner.\n    *   Go to \"Settings and privacy\"\n    *   Scroll down to \"Who can see your content\" and tap \"Story and Reel sharing\".\n    *   Choose options like:\n        *   **Close Friends:**  Share stories/Reels only with a selected list of close friends.\n        *   **Hide Story From:**  Specifically hide your stories from certain people.\n\n**3. Facebook Settings and Privacy:**\n\n*   **Review Your Facebook Privacy Settings:** While disconnecting helps, review your Facebook settings as they might indirectly affect your Instagram visibility. Pay attention to:\n    *   **Who can see your posts?** Make sure it's set to \"Friends\" or \"Only Me\".\n    *   **Who can look you up using the email address or phone number you provided?** Set this to \"Friends\" or \"Only Me.\"  This prevents Facebook from suggesting your profile (and potentially linked Instagram) to people who have your contact info.\n    *   **Do you want search engines outside of Facebook to link to your profile?** Disable this.\n\n**4. Preventing Instagram From Syncing Contacts:**\n\n*   **Check Your Instagram Settings:**\n    *   Go to your Profile.\n    *   Tap the three horizontal lines (menu icon) in the top right corner.\n    *   Go to \"Settings and privacy\"\n    *   Tap \"Account Centre\" at the very top\n    *   Tap \"Your information and permissions\"\n    *   Tap \"Upload Contacts\"\n    *   Toggle \"Connect Contacts\" **OFF**.\n\n    *   *This prevents Instagram from continuously uploading your phone's contact list to find potential friends.  If it's already off, you're good. If it's on, turn it off and consider deleting any previously uploaded contacts (there's an option to do that).*\n\n**5. Blocking (Use Sparingly):**\n\n*   **Block Specific Individuals:**  If you absolutely want to prevent certain Facebook friends from finding you on Instagram, blocking them is a direct solution.\n    *   Go to their profile (if you can find them).\n    *   Tap the three dots in the top right corner.\n    *   Select \"Block.\"\n    *  *Blocking prevents them from seeing your profile at all, even if it's public, and prevents them from contacting you.*\n\n**6. Consider a Separate Email/Phone:**\n\n*   **For a High Level of Separation:** If you're *extremely* concerned about privacy, consider creating a separate email address or using a different phone number for your Instagram account than the one you use for Facebook.  This makes it much harder for the two platforms to link your accounts based on contact information.\n\n**Important Considerations and Caveats:**\n\n*   **Mutual Friends:**  Even with all these precautions, mutual friends can still see if you're both following the same accounts or if you both like/comment on the same posts.  There's no way to completely hide your existence from people you know.\n*   **Manual Searching:**  If someone *really* wants to find you, they can still manually search for your username (if they know it) or try searching for names that might be similar to yours.\n*   **Shared Groups:** If you and your Facebook friends are in the same Instagram groups (e.g., photography groups, fan groups), they may still see your posts within those groups.\n*   **Reverse Image Search:** Someone could potentially take a public photo of you (from Facebook, for example) and use reverse image search to try and find your Instagram profile.  This is a rare scenario, but it's a possibility.\n\n**In Summary:**\n\nThe best strategy is to disconnect your accounts, make your Instagram private, disable contact syncing, and review your Facebook privacy settings.  While you can't guarantee 100% privacy, these steps will significantly reduce the chances of your Facebook friends and contacts easily finding you on Instagram.  Be mindful of what you post and who you interact with, and adjust your settings based on your comfort level.\n",
